# Trivy ignore list — base-OS CVEs in the RUNTIME image base
# gcr.io/distroless/nodejs22-debian13:nonroot (Debian 13 "trixie"), i.e. what
# `trivy image` actually scans (the node:26-slim build stage is not shipped).
# Every entry: NO fixed version available in trixie AND no runtime path in our
# Node-only proto server (distroless: no shell, no perl, nothing but node + libs).
# Each is an accepted, documented risk; re-review whenever the base image digest
# is bumped (SEC-1 baseline discipline; ties to audit SD-5.1 / F-15).
#
# Reviewed 2026-07-10 (SEC-1): previous entries (bookworm perl/ncurses/zlib-minizip
# from the old node:22-slim single-stage image) no longer apply to the distroless
# runtime and were removed after the trivy-image scan came back to life (the
# corepack build break had silently disabled it — caught by the SEC-1 gate).

# libc6 2.41-12+deb13u3 — MEDIUM, no fixed version published for trixie yet.
CVE-2026-5435
CVE-2026-5450
CVE-2026-5928
CVE-2026-6238

# libc6 — ancient LOW, disputed/won't-fix upstream (Debian marks them minor/unimportant),
# no fixed version; carried by every glibc-based image.
CVE-2010-4756
CVE-2018-20796
CVE-2019-1010022
CVE-2019-1010023
CVE-2019-1010024
CVE-2019-1010025
CVE-2019-9192

# zlib1g 1:1.3.dfsg+really1.3.1-1+b1 — MEDIUM, no fixed version for trixie.
CVE-2026-27171
